  This is a solid real-world Terraform-based CI/CD infrastructure project. In an interview, you don’t want to just list folders—you want to explain it like a system design story: problem → architecture → flow → why choices were made → tradeoffs.

Here’s a clean way to explain it.

🧠 1. One-line project summary (start here)

“I built a fully automated CI/CD pipeline on AWS using Terraform, where code changes trigger a pipeline that builds a Docker image, pushes it to ECR, and deploys it to EC2 instances running Nginx.”

This sets the tone immediately.

🏗️ 2. High-level architecture (what you designed)

Break it into 5 layers:

☁️ Infrastructure layer (Terraform modules)
vpc/ → networking (subnets, routing, IGW, etc.)
ec2/ → compute layer where app runs
ecr/ → Docker image repository
iam/ → permissions for CodeBuild, CodeDeploy, EC2
codebuild/ → build Docker images
codedeploy/ → deploy app to EC2
codepipeline/ → orchestrates the whole CI/CD flow

👉 “Everything is modularized using Terraform for reusability and separation of concerns.”

🔄 3. CI/CD flow (MOST IMPORTANT PART)

Explain this like a story:

🚀 Step 1: Code push triggers pipeline
Developer pushes code to GitHub (or CodeCommit)
codepipeline detects the change and starts execution

🔨 Step 2: Build stage (CodeBuild)

Inside modules/codebuild:

Code is pulled from pipeline
buildspec.yml runs:
builds Docker image using Dockerfile
tags image with commit/version
logs into ECR
pushes image to ECR repo

👉 Output:

Docker image stored in ECR

📦 Step 3: Artifact passing
CodePipeline passes build output to next stage
No manual intervention

🚀 Step 4: Deploy stage (CodeDeploy)

Inside modules/codedeploy:

CodeDeploy connects to EC2 instances (via agent)
Uses appspec.yml
Runs deployment hooks:
stop old container
pull latest image from ECR
run new container using deploy.sh

🖥️ Step 5: Application runs on EC2

Inside modules/ec2:

EC2 instances are created in VPC
user_data.sh installs:
Docker
CodeDeploy agent
Nginx container runs and serves app on port 80

📦 4. Supporting components explanation
🐳 ECR (modules/ecr)
Stores Docker images
Acts as versioned container registry

🔐 IAM (modules/iam)
Gives permissions to:
CodeBuild → push to ECR
CodeDeploy → deploy to EC2
EC2 → pull images from ECR

🌐 VPC (modules/vpc)
Creates isolated network:
public/private subnets
routing
internet access for EC2

⚙️ Terraform root module (terraform/)
Orchestrates all modules:
calls VPC
creates EC2
connects CodePipeline → CodeBuild → CodeDeploy

🔁 5. End-to-end CI/CD flow (simple interview diagram in words)

You can say:

GitHub Push
   ↓
CodePipeline triggers
   ↓
CodeBuild builds Docker image
   ↓
Push image to ECR
   ↓
CodeDeploy pulls image on EC2
   ↓
deploy.sh runs container
   ↓
Nginx app goes live on port 80
